{
  "doc_id": "50937",
  "text": "An increase in outbreaks related to raw milk contaminated by a variety of pathogens has been observed [CITATION_1] . Pasteurisation is a well-known and effective way to eliminate pathogens and bacteria from raw milk, decreasing the risk of disease transmission [CITATION_2] . THL and the Finnish Food Safety Authority Evira recommend that children, the elderly, pregnant women and persons with a severe primary disease should heattreat raw milk before consumption. In this study, age was associated with illness: those under 23 years of age were more likely to get ill. By contrast, previously diagnosed chronic diseases did not affect the probability of YP infection. Our results are in line with findings from a study showing that healthy adults can become infected by consuming contaminated raw milk [CITATION_3] , and we suggest that also adults should heat raw milk before consuming it.",
